		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30056157">Timeskips can be useful. If you have a story that spans through many years, what did people expect? Tons of chapters/episodes where nothing happens, while waiting for the next plot-relevant event? <br />
I am, however, obviously talking about consistent and planned stories like Oyasumi Punpun, Eden: it's an Endless World, Shinsekai Yori, and so on. It just shows that timeskips themselves are not bad at all, what matters is what purpose the writer gives them. If it's for powering up, skipping arcs and plot points, suddenly changing stuff made up on the spot to contrivedly choose a direction for the story, then yeah, you get yourself an example of bad writing.<br />
<br />
<!--quote--><div class="quotetext"><strong>Aryaragi said:</strong><!--quotesaid--><br> Two shows that  come to mind that would constantly use time skips for conveniences is Shinsekai Yaoi and SAO.. hated both of them..<!--quote--></div><br />
