		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30074627">SAO's timeskips tried to skip over what might have been some tedious level grinding episodes, the problem is after a lot of them there wasn't enough context and some plot threads were forgotten about entirely. SSY's timeskips left you completely in the dark but considering certain plot points it actually made sense.<br />
<br />
I don't mind 'em, but at the top of my head I only remember the two shows I mentioned previously, Naruto, and Eden of the East. Naruto was basically an excuse to draw everyone older and give bigger attacks, while Eden of the East's timeframe is p seamless going into its movies.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/vqw0XUz.png" /></div></td>
