		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30108565">Timeskips, huh. First thing I'm reminded of here is shonen, and the result tends to be rather poorly executed, though how poorly executed depends on the series. Naruto comes to mind when it comes to poor execution, the examples being given by Nagisa33 above.<br />
On the other hand, we have timeskips which are not bad on their own, but pave the way for lackluster sequels/continuations. Dragon Ball Z and One Piece have decent timeskips on their own, but lackluster arcs after the first halves for both series make the build-up in the first halves rather pointless. <br />
And then there are timeskips with little to no continuity between them. SAO. I don't need any explanation for this one.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/8NuZt.png" /></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
